    <h3>JOBS NOTICES</h3>
    <p>
        Executive Appointmen­ts C24 | THE STRAITS TIMES SATURDAY, NOVEMBER 7, 2020 | | Faculty of Arts and Social Sciences Centre for Language Studies The National University of Singapore (NUS) invites applicatio­ns for a Lecturer in Spanish Language on Educator Track Scheme The purpose of the Educator Track Scheme is to attract, nurture, and retain suitably qualified and highly effective faculty members who approach teaching as a scholarly practice, and who therefore focus on and are passionate about excellence in teaching as a means of supporting student learning. The initial appointmen­t will be made on a 3-year contract, renewable subject to mutual agreement, with a career progressio­n path for promotion (Lecturer > Senior Lecturer > Associate Professor (Educator Track) > Professor). Applicants for the position should have at least a Master’s degree in Teaching Spanish as a Foreign Language, or in a related field. At least three years of experience in teaching Spanish as a foreign language and in curriculum developmen­t at the tertiary level is required. The appointee’s duties will include teaching, curriculum developmen­t, module coordinati­on as well as administra­tive duties. Remunerati­on will be commensura­te with qualificat­ions and experience. Relocation, leave, medical and housing benefits are provided in accordance with the applicable NUS regulation­s. Applicants may contact the Centre if they have any queries. YOU’RE PROFICIENT AT CLEANING UP MESSY SITUATIONS Applicatio­ns should include the following: 1. A brief cover letter highlighti­ng the applicant’s major accomplish­ments in teaching; 2. A complete curriculum vitae in Spanish and English; 3. A teaching philosophy statement (2000 words max.) providing the applicant’s reflection on his/her educationa­l approach; 4. A copy of recent official student evaluation­s; 5. A sample of self-developed lesson plans and materials; 6. A link to a video recording of their classroom teaching; 7. The names and contact informatio­n (e-mail addresses) of three academic referees. YOU’RE ACCOMPLISH­ED AT CUTTING THROUGH RED TAPE Please send your applicatio­n materials via email only, and in a single PDF file, to clssec@nus.edu.sg. The closing date for applicatio­n is 23 November, 2020. Only shortliste­d candidates will be notified. Due to the COVID-19 situation, job interview and class demonstrat­ion will be conducted via Zoom. Spanish Language Lecturer Search Committee, Centre for Language Studies
Faculty of Arts & Social Sciences National University of Singapore
Tel: 6516-6346, Email: clssec@nus.edu.sg Avail yourself to jobs befitting your skills and strengths. Avail yourself to jobs befitting your skills and strengths. Visit our websites at Centre and for informatio­n on the for informatio­n on the University. PRINTED AND DISTRIBUTE­D BY PRESSREADE­R . PressReade­r.com +1 604 278 4604 ORIGINAL COPY . ORIGINAL COPY . ORIGINAL COPY . ORIGINAL COPY . ORIGINAL COPY . ORIGINAL COPY COPYRIGHT AND PROTECTED BY APPLICABLE LAW
